DETERIORATING WX WAS ENCOUNTERED AS THE PILOT FOLLOWED A HIGHWAY TO 
HIS DEST ON AN EASTERLY HEADING. ON SCENE EVIDENCE INDICATED THAT THE 
AIRCRAFT IMPACTED LEFT WING TIP FIRST ON A NORTHERLY HEADING NEAR THE EAST 
END OF A BOX CANYON. THE IMPACT FLIGHT PATH ANGLE WAS ESTIMATED TO BE 25 
TO 30 DEGREES DOWN. THE BOX CANYON IN WHICH THE ACCIDENT OCCURRED WAS 
8 MI SOUTH OF THE HIGHWAY. LANDER COUNTY OFFICIALS IN AUSTIN OBSERVED 
THE WX TO BE OBSCURED WITH FOG. 
